\title{Span and Spans}
\taxon{Definition}

\p{The \strong{span} of a list of vectors in #{V} is denoted and defined by,
##{\text{span}(v_1,\dots,v_m)=\{a_1 v_1+\dots+a_m v_m;a_m \in \mathbb{F} a\}}
We define the span of the empty list as #{\{0\}}.
}
\p{It is easy to see that the span of a list of vectors in #{V} is the smallest subspace cantaining all of the listed vectors.}

\p{If the span of a list of vectors equals #{V}, we say that the list \em{spans} #{V}.}
